ries of Riel’s surrender/capture, and, with the inclusion of Armstrong’s unpublished memoir, allows this consummate storyteller to speak in his own voice.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFrontier and pioneer lifezWest (U.S.). 0aRiel Rebellion, 1885xScouts and scouting. 0aWyandot IndiansvBiography. 7aHISTORY / United States / State & Local / Southwest (AZ, NM, OK, TX).2bisacsh  aHuron.  aLouis Riel.  aWyandot.  abuffalo.  afrontier.  ahunt.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311127365508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017z978311127619940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978088977462940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780889774629423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780889774629/original  a978-3-11-127365-5  ACUP Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-127619-9  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles